Ho, ho, ho!

201
00:08:53,185 --> 00:08:55,586
- What's your name?
- Brittany.

202
00:08:55,654 --> 00:08:57,488
You've gotten really tan.

203
00:08:57,556 --> 00:09:00,424
That's because at the North Pole
there's a hole in the ozone.

204
00:09:00,492 --> 00:09:02,426
(laughs)
You're amazing.

205
00:09:02,494 --> 00:09:04,462
I know you're really busy,

206
00:09:04,529 --> 00:09:07,665
so I only want one
thing for Christmas.

207
00:09:07,733 --> 00:09:10,968
Do you see my
boyfriend over there?

208
00:09:11,036 --> 00:09:14,906
For Christmas, I want
him to be able to walk.

209
00:09:16,141 --> 00:09:17,508
You can do that,
can't you, Santa?

210
00:09:22,681 --> 00:09:25,983
Sure... I'm on it.

211
00:09:26,051 --> 00:09:29,253
- Thank you so much, Santa.
- Now we're screwed.

212
00:09:33,642 --> 00:09:36,460
Now, remember,
it has to be lush and romantic.

213
00:09:36,528 --> 00:09:38,229
Why?

214
00:09:38,280 --> 00:09:41,832
Because I am very specific
when I give a gift.

215
00:09:41,900 --> 00:09:43,401
You don't know how many kittens

216
00:09:43,468 --> 00:09:46,203
I've given away because they
haven't been just right.

217
00:09:46,271 --> 00:09:49,373
So, do you like my
winter wonderland?

218
00:09:49,441 --> 00:09:52,043
Well, I don't really like
artificial Christmas trees.

219
00:09:52,110 --> 00:09:53,477
I like real ones.

220
00:09:53,545 --> 00:09:55,513
They smell amazing.
That's kind of the whole point.

221
00:09:55,580 --> 00:09:58,416
Right.

222
00:09:58,483 --> 00:09:59,917
Anyway...

223
00:10:03,621 --> 00:10:05,022
