heartbreak,

239
00:10:51,887 --> 00:10:56,007
just like on Broadway,
the show must go on.

240
00:10:56,074 --> 00:10:59,610
Besides, the AV Club worked so
hard on the snow.

241
00:11:01,013 --> 00:11:04,615
♪ Greeting cards
have all been sent. ♪

242
00:11:04,682 --> 00:11:08,819
♪ The Christmas rush
is through. ♪

243
00:11:08,870 --> 00:11:14,041
♪ But I still have
one wish to make: ♪

244
00:11:14,126 --> 00:11:18,229
♪ A special one for you. ♪

245
00:11:20,132 --> 00:11:25,920
♪ Merry Christmas, darling. ♪

246
00:11:26,004 --> 00:11:31,008
♪ We're apart, that's true. ♪

247
00:11:31,076 --> 00:11:36,814
♪ But I can dream,
and in my dreams, ♪

248
00:11:36,881 --> 00:11:42,219
♪ I'm Christmasing with you. ♪

249
00:11:42,270 --> 00:11:47,724
♪ Holidays are joyful. ♪

250
00:11:47,776 --> 00:11:53,431
♪ There's always something new. ♪

251
00:11:53,498 --> 00:12:04,508
♪ But every day's a holiday
when I'm near to you. ♪

252
00:12:04,576 --> 00:12:08,379
♪ Oh, the lights on my tree, ♪

253
00:12:08,447 --> 00:12:11,348
♪ I wish you could see. ♪

254
00:12:11,416 --> 00:12:14,018
♪ I wish it every day. ♪

255
00:12:14,085 --> 00:12:16,587
♪ Ah-ah-ah-ah... ♪

256
00:12:16,655 --> 00:12:22,460
♪ And the logs on the fire
fill me with desire ♪

257
00:12:22,527 --> 00:12:27,498
♪ to see you and to say ♪

258
00:12:27,566 --> 00:12:34,538
♪ that I wish you Merry Christmas. ♪
♪ Merry Christmas, darling... ♪

259
00:12:34,606 --> 00:12:39,126
♪ Happy New Year, too. ♪

260
00:12:39,211 --> 00:12:44,081
♪ I've just one wish
on this Christmas Eve: ♪

261
00:12:44,149 --> 00:12:45,616
♪ On this Christmas Eve... ♪

262
00:12:45,684 --> 00:12:52,089
♪ I wish I were with you. ♪

263
00:12:52,157 --> 00:12:54,592
♪ I wish I were... ♪

264
00:12:54,659 --> 00:12:56,594
♪ with... ♪

265
00:12:56,645 --> 00:13:00,848
♪ You... ♪
♪ Merry Christmas, Merry Christmas. ♪

266
00:13:00,932 --> 00:13:02,566
♪ Merry Christmas... ♪

267
00:13:02,634 --> 00:13:06,370
♪ Merry Christmas... ♪
♪ Merry Christmas... ♪

268
00:13:06,438 --> 00:13:14,695
♪ Darling... ♪
♪ Darling... ♪

269
00:13:32,697 --> 00:13:35,099
(sighs)

270
00:13:36,668 --> 00:13:38,235
(thud)

271
00:13:38,303 --> 00:13:39,236
Hey.

272
00:13:39,304 --> 00:13:40,838
You scared me.

273
00:13:40,906 --> 00:13:43,541
Good. Because I'm
actually Marley's ghost, and

274
00:13:43,608 --> 00:13:46,009
(whispers):
I'm here to tell you

275
00:13:46,061 --> 00:13:48,012
to stop studying so hard.

276
00:13:48,079 --> 00:13:49,647
KURT:
Hmm. What's with the boom box?

277
00:13:49,714 --> 00:13:52,049
I need you to sing with me.
Well, rehearse with me.

278
00:13:52,117 --> 00:13:54,451
I got a gig singing
"Baby, It's Cold Outside"

279
00:13:54,519 --> 00:13:56,287
in the King's Island
Christmas Spectacular.

280
00:13:56,354 --> 00:13:58,055
Ah, a personal favorite.

281
00:13:58,123 --> 00:14:00,758
Too bad they'd never
let us sing it together.

282
00:14:00,825 --> 00:14:03,561
I mean, as two... artists.

283
00:14:03,628 --> 00:14:06,430
Mmm. So you going to
help me out here?

284
00:14:06,498 --> 00:14:08,299
Anything to get me to stop
reading about Charlemagne.

285
00:14:08,366 --> 00:14:10,100
Very good, then.

286
00:14:11,436 --> 00:14:14,505
("Baby, It's Cold Outside"
begins)

287
00:14:20,078 --> 00:14:22,079
♪ I really can't stay. ♪

288
00:14:22,147 --> 00:14:24,582
♪ But baby,
it's cold outside. ♪

289
00:14:24,649 --> 00:14:26,049
♪ I've got to go away. ♪

290
00:14:26,101 --> 00:14:28,219
♪ But baby, it's cold outside. ♪

291
00:14:28,286 --> 00:14:29,787
♪ This evening has been... ♪

292
00:14:29,854 --> 00:14:32,823
♪ Been hoping that
you'd drop in. ♪

293
00:14:32,891 --> 00:14:36,927
♪ So very nice. ♪
♪ I'll hold your hands, ♪

294
00:14:36,995 --> 00:14:38,762
♪ they're just like ice. ♪

295
00:14:38,830 --> 00:14:40,664
♪ My mother will
start to worry. ♪

296
00:14:40,732 --> 00:14:42,099
♪ Beautiful,
what's your hurry? ♪

297
00:14:42,167 --> 00:14:45,035
♪ My father will be
pacing the floor. ♪

298
00:14:45,103 --> 00:14:47,471
♪ Listen to the fireplace roar. ♪

299
00:14:47,539 --> 00:14:49,607
♪ So really, I'd better scurry. ♪

300
00:14:49,674 --> 00:14:51,308
♪ Beautiful,
please don't hurry. ♪

301
00:14:51,376 --> 00:14:53,310
♪ But maybe just
half a drink more. ♪

302
00:14:53,378 --> 00:14:55,746
♪ Put some records
on while I pour. ♪

303
00:14:55,814 --> 00:14:59,250
♪ The neighbors might faint. ♪
♪ Baby, it's bad out there. ♪

304
00:14:59,317 --> 00:15:00,818
♪ Say, what's in this drink? ♪

305
00:15:00,885 --> 00:15:03,821
♪ No cabs to be had out there. ♪

306
00:15:03,888 --> 00:15:06,923
♪ I wish I knew how... ♪
♪ Your eyes are like starlight now. ♪

307
00:15:06,975 --> 00:15:08,642
♪ To break this spell. ♪

308
00:15:08,727 --> 00:15:13,230
♪ I'll take your hat,
your hair looks swell. ♪

309
00:15:13,298 --> 00:15:15,466
♪ I ought to say
"No, no, no, sir." ♪

310
00:15:15,533 --> 00:15:17,434
♪ Mind if I move in closer? ♪

311
00:15:17,502 --> 00:15:19,570
♪ At least I'm gonna
say that I tried. ♪

312
00:15:19,638 --> 00:15:21,322
♪ What's the sense
in hurting my pride? ♪

313
00:15:21,406 --> 00:15:22,706
♪ I really can't stay. ♪

314
00:15:22,774 --> 00:15:24,508
♪ Baby, don't hold out. ♪

315
00:15:24,576 --> 00:15:29,446
BOTH:
♪ Oh, but it's cold outside. ♪

316
00:15:32,984 --> 00:15:35,286
♪ I've gotta get home. ♪

317
00:15:35,353 --> 00:15:38,222
♪ But baby,
you'd freeze out there. ♪

318
00:15:38,290 --> 00:15:40,190
♪ Say, lend me a coat. ♪

319
00:15:40,258 --> 00:15:42,159
♪ It's up to your knees
out there. ♪

320
00:15:42,227 --> 00:15:43,527
♪ You've really been grand. ♪

321
00:15:43,595 --> 00:15:45,696
♪ I thrill when
you touch my hand. ♪

322
00:15:45,764 --> 00:15:47,398
♪ But don't you see? ♪

323
00:15:47,465 --> 00:15:51,869
♪ How can you do
this thing to me? ♪

324
00:15:51,936 --> 00:15:53,771
♪ There's bound to be
talk tomorrow. ♪

325
00:15:53,838 --> 00:15:55,539
♪ Think of my
life-long sorrow... ♪

326
00:15:55,607 --> 00:15:57,608
♪ At least there will be
plenty implied. ♪

327
00:15:57,676 --> 00:16:00,044
♪ If you got pneumonia
and died. ♪

328
00:16:00,111 --> 00:16:01,812
♪ I really can't stay. ♪

329
00:16:01,880 --> 00:16:04,148
♪ Get over that hold out. ♪

330
00:16:07,085 --> 00:16:11,255
♪ Ooh, baby, it's cold... ♪
♪ Oh, but it's cold... ♪

331
00:16:11,323 --> 00:16:17,127
♪ Outside! ♪
♪ Outside! ♪

332
00:16:20,365 --> 00:16:21,598
I think you're ready.

333
00:16:23,001 --> 00:16:25,269
Well, for the record,

334
00:16:25,337 --> 00:16:27,671
you are much better than
that girl's going to be.

335
00:16:30,141 --> 00:16:32,343
Hey.

336
00:16:32,410 --> 00:16:34,111
Mr. Schuester.

337
00:16:34,179 --> 00:16:35,379
(both chuckling)

338
00:16:35,447 --> 00:16:37,715
Oh, good to see you, Kurt.

339
00:16:37,782 --> 00:16:39,182
Someone special?

340
00:16:40,385 --> 00:16:41,785
No, just a friend.

341
00:16:41,853 --> 00:16:44,021
But on the upside,
I am in love with him,

342
00:16:44,089 --> 00:16:46,056
and he's actually gay.
I call that progress.

343
00:16:46,124 --> 00:16:48,592
(sighs)
How you doing?

344
00:16:48,660 --> 00:16:50,594
Classes are harder,
but the kids are kinder.

345
00:16:50,662 --> 00:16:52,496
But I miss you guys a lot,
though.

346
00:16:52,564 --> 00:16:53,997
So what brings you here?

347
00:16:54,065 --> 00:16:55,766
Are you looking
for teaching at a place

348
00:16:55,834 --> 00:16:57,534
where pencils aren't
primarily used as weapons?

349
00:16:57,602 --> 00:17:00,871
Actually, I need
some holiday help.

350
00:17:00,939 --> 00:17:03,073
I don't know if you know this,

351
00:17:03,141 --> 00:17:05,943
but I am really bad
at Christmas shopping.

352
00:17:09,347 --> 00:17:11,081
Oh, honey,
just what I wanted.

353
00:17:11,149 --> 00:17:13,550
Jumper cables.

354
00:17:13,618 --> 00:17:16,553
This year, I drew Sue
in the office pool Secret Santa.

355
00:17:16,621 --> 00:17:19,790
And I tell you,
I can't think of anything good.

356
00:17:19,858 --> 00:17:21,225
And you are so great
at shopping,

357
00:17:21,292 --> 00:17:23,861
- I thought I'd...
- I have the perfect idea.

358
00:17:23,928 --> 00:17:25,729
(school bell ringing)

359
00:17:25,797 --> 00:17:28,165
I think I can tell
who wrapped that.

360
00:17:28,233 --> 00:17:29,333
Who's it for?

361
00:17:29,401 --> 00:17:30,601
Oh, Sue.

362
00:17:30,668 --> 00:17:32,870
I drew her as my Secret Santa.

363
00:17:32,937 --> 00:17:35,139
Wait a minute.
That's not possible.

364
00:17:35,206 --> 00:17:39,343
- Sue's my Secret Santa.
- No, Sue's my Secret Santa.

365
00:17:39,411 --> 00:17:42,146
I'm everybody's Secret Santa.

366
00:17:42,213 --> 00:17:43,947
Yeah, you can just
drop those wherever.

367
00:17:44,015 --> 00:17:45,649
You rigged Secret Santa?

368
00:17:45,717 --> 00:17:47,418
How? It was my idea.

369
00:17:47,485 --> 00:17:49,319
Well, you're not the only person
at this school

370
00:17:49,387 --> 00:17:51,054
who consumes protein powder
by the tubful.

371
00:17:52,590 --> 00:17:54,725
<i>Remember when I told you
I was taking</i>

372
00:17:54,793 --> 00:17:57,828
<i>all those science textbooks
to an exorcist?</i>

373
00:17:57,896 --> 00:17:59,997
<i>Well, that's what we call
a diversion.</i>

374
00:18:04,502 --> 00:18:06,737
You filled your tub
with your name only.

375
00:18:06,805 --> 00:18:07,905
You're a regular
Agatha Christie,

376
00:18:07,972 --> 00:18:09,940
except even more sexless.

377
00:18:10,008 --> 00:18:13,877
See, people, I hate Christmas,
but I love presents.

378
00:18:13,945 --> 00:18:14,912
Ah, look at this.

379
00:18:14,979 --> 00:18:16,413
It's a track suit

380
00:18:16,481 --> 00:18:18,482
with a fur-lined hood
for the winter months.

381
00:18:18,550 --> 00:18:19,683
Thanks, fella.

382
00:18:19,751 --> 00:18:20,684
That was Kurt's idea.

383
00:18:20,752 --> 00:18:21,785
Ah-ah-ah, William.

384
00:18:21,853 --> 00:18:23,120
These gifts are legally mine.

385
00:18:23,188 --> 00:18:25,189
Now, you may or may
not be aware of this,

386
00:18:25,256 --> 00:18:27,290
but I'm an honorary officer
of the Lima Police Department,

387
00:18:27,342 --> 00:18:29,343
and if you take my property
out of my office,

388
00:18:29,427 --> 00:18:31,695
I will pick up that phone and
have you arrested for theft.

389
00:18:31,763 --> 00:18:34,164
We are not going to let you
steal Christmas, Sue.

390
00:18:34,232 --> 00:18:36,467
- You're not going to get away with this.
- I think I already have.

391
00:18:36,534 --> 00:18:39,036
William, Elmo, you,

392
00:18:39,103 --> 00:18:40,704
get the hell out of my office.

393
00:18:42,340 --> 00:18:45,242
I just got to say, this
is a really expensive blender.

394
00:18:45,310 --> 00:18:47,311
It's top of the line.

395
00:18:55,753 --> 00:18:57,120
(school bell ringing)

396
00:18:57,188 --> 00:18:58,322
At ease, Becky.

397
00:18:59,728 --> 00:19:01,663
(school bell ringing)

398
00:19:05,234 --> 00:19:07,435
I'm gonna stop you right here.
Why are you wearing that hat?

399
00:19:07,503 --> 00:19:08,837
Because it's Christmas
and it's fun.

400
00:19:08,904 --> 00:19:10,505
No, it's offensive.
You're wearing a Santa Claus hat,

401
00:19:10,573 --> 00:19:12,407
and yet you're handing me
no gifts. I need gifts.

402
00:19:12,474 --> 00:19:13,942
- You want my hat?
- It's a start.

403
00:19:16,445 --> 00:19:17,445
Coach, we've got a problem.

404
00:19:19,081 --> 00:19:20,215
WILL:
Thanks, guys.

405
00:19:20,282 --> 00:19:22,383
Those go under the tree
in the choir room.

406
00:19:22,451 --> 00:19:24,586
Plop it down there.
Thank you.

407
00:19:24,653 --> 00:19:26,054
Can you believe it?

408
00:19:26,121 --> 00:19:28,690
Six different people
got Sue a Shake Weight.

409
00:19:28,757 --> 00:19:30,892
Mmm.

410
00:19:30,960 --> 00:19:32,660
Becky, go into the glove box
of my LeCar

411
00:19:32,728 --> 00:19:35,797
and bring me my tear gas.
Then, get me Gloria Allred.

412
00:19:36,999 --> 00:19:38,566
Merry Christmas, Sue.

413
00:19:38,634 --> 00:19:40,401
As you can see, we're
repo'ing your gifts.

414
00:19:40,469 --> 00:19:42,537
Most can't be returned

415
00:19:42,605 --> 00:19:44,706
since you inexplicably opened
all of them.

416
00:19:44,773 --> 00:19:46,674
And I licked each one
so no one would touch them.

417
00:19:46,742 --> 00:19:48,176
So the staff has
agreed to donate them

418
00:19:48,244 --> 00:19:50,311
to the homeless kids
at McKinney-Vento.

419
00:19:50,379 --> 00:19:51,779
I mean, what is your
problem anyway?

420
00:19:51,847 --> 00:19:53,381
Were you one
of those kids

421
00:19:53,449 --> 00:19:54,749
who never got presents
at Christmas?

422
00:19:54,817 --> 00:19:57,051
Yes, Dr. Laura.
As a matter of fact, I was,

423
00:19:57,119 --> 00:19:58,686
and I'm making up for it now.

424
00:19:58,754 --> 00:20:00,221
Face it, Sue. We won.

425
00:20:00,289 --> 00:20:02,357
This will not stand.

426
00:20:02,424 --> 00:20:04,993
I have legal rights
to those gifts.

427
00:20:05,060 --> 00:20:06,427
You know what, Sue?
You don't.

428
00:20:06,495 --> 00:20:07,862
I checked with
Human Resources,

429
00:20:07,930 --> 00:20:09,564
and because you
misrepresented yourself,

430
00:20:09,632 --> 00:20:12,367
it is within our legal right
to take back these gifts.

431
00:20:12,434 --> 00:20:14,702
Ho, ho, ho.

432
00:20:15,871 --> 00:20:17,038
(Beiste chuckling)

433
00:20:19,541 --> 00:20:21,609
You know what you are, Sue?

434
00:20:21,677 --> 00:20:22,710
You're a grinch.

435
00:20:27,950 --> 00:20:29,417
Are you guys punking me?

436
00:20:29,485 --> 00:20:31,419
I thought we were cool after
you sang me that song.

437
00:20:31,487 --> 00:20:33,154
This is serious, Coach.

438
00:20:33,222 --> 00:20:35,390
Remember when you were a kid,
the way you felt

439
00:20:35,457 --> 00:20:37,025
when you came downstairs
on Christmas morning,

440
00:20:37,092 --> 00:20:38,426
seeing that Santa had come?

441
00:20:38,494 --> 00:20:40,228
I do love Santa Claus.

442
00:20:40,296 --> 00:20:42,830
One year, I asked him
for a full set of free weights.

443
00:20:42,898 --> 00:20:45,300
Kept asking my dad,
"How did Santy get

444
00:20:45,367 --> 00:20:46,801
those 75-pound dumbbells
down the chimney?"

445
00:20:46,869 --> 00:20:48,903
Should have suspected something

446
00:20:48,971 --> 00:20:51,105
when Dad was in traction
until the end of January.

447
00:20:51,173 --> 00:20:52,840
You've got the perfect
Santa body type.

448
00:20:52,908 --> 00:20:53,908
Watch it, Puckerman.

449
00:20:53,976 --> 00:20:55,443
Look, we rented the suit.

450
00:20:55,511 --> 00:20:56,644
All you need to do
is put it on.

451
00:20:56,712 --> 00:20:58,579
Just tell her
that you can't give her

452
00:20:58,647 --> 00:21:00,081
the gift of me
walking this year.

453
00:21:00,149 --> 00:21:02,116
That seems so harsh
and not at all like Santa.

454
00:21:02,184 --> 00:21:03,635
She asked Santa
for the impossible:

455
00:21:03,719 --> 00:21:05,119
Me walking again.

456
00:21:05,187 --> 00:21:07,055
If Christmas morning
comes around and I'm not

457
00:21:07,122 --> 00:21:09,891
dancing in Glee Club rehearsal
with no personal explanation

458
00:21:09,959 --> 00:21:12,226
from her idol, she's going
to lose faith in Old Saint Nick,

459
00:21:12,294 --> 00:21:13,628
and we can't have that.

460
00:21:13,696 --> 00:21:15,063
Tell her the elves
are working on it.

461
00:21:15,130 --> 00:21:17,865
Elves have awesome cord blood
for stem cell research,

462
00:21:17,933 --> 00:21:20,101
but these advances
are a few years away.

463
00:21:21,303 --> 00:21:22,704
Okay.

464
00:21:22,771 --> 00:21:25,039
Great. And then we need you
to break into her house.

465
00:21:25,107 --> 00:21:26,908
- What? No, no way!
- The back door will be open.

466
00:21:26,976 --> 00:21:30,745
I talked to her parents. They
really want her to believe, too.

467
00:21:30,813 --> 00:21:32,813
(school bell ringing)

468
00:21:32,865 --> 00:21:34,382
BECKY:
Look, Coach.

469
00:21:34,450 --> 00:21:36,751
The janitor staff
got you hideous gloves.

470
00:21:36,818 --> 00:21:38,219
SUE:
Give me those.

471
00:21:38,287 --> 00:21:39,587
They'll come in handy.

472
00:21:39,655 --> 00:21:41,356
No fingerprints.

473
00:21:41,423 --> 00:21:43,558
Suit up, Becky.

474
00:21:43,625 --> 00:21:47,295
I don't understand
why we have to dress up, Coach.

475
00:21:47,346 --> 00:21:50,465
Well, this way,
if anyone sees us,

476
00:21:50,532 --> 00:21:53,134
we'll have plausible
deniability.

477
00:21:53,202 --> 00:21:55,236
I repeat, you are a "rein-dog."

478
00:21:55,304 --> 00:21:57,138
Trust me, they're real.

479
00:21:57,206 --> 00:21:58,106
How am I looking?

480
00:21:58,173 --> 00:21:59,140
Fantastic, Coach.

481
00:21:59,208 --> 00:22:01,042
Yeah, you know, Becky,

482
00:22:01,110 --> 00:22:03,177
my mastery of camouflage
is the only thing

483
00:22:03,245 --> 00:22:04,862
that kept me
from being court-martialed

484
00:22:04,947 --> 00:22:06,981
after that My Lai
misunderstanding.

485
00:22:07,049 --> 00:22:08,282
Copy that.

486
00:22:08,350 --> 00:22:10,818
Now, let's go get
what is rightfully mine.

487
00:22:10,886 --> 00:22:12,553
Schuester thinks I'm a grinch,

488
00:22:12,621 --> 00:22:14,188
well, that's exactly
what he's gonna get.

489
00:22:14,256 --> 00:22:16,124
("You're A Mean One, Mr. Grinch"
playing)

490
00:22:16,191 --> 00:22:17,458
(wheels squeaking)

491
00:22:20,212 --> 00:22:25,049
♪ You're a mean one,
Sue the Grinch. ♪

492
00:22:25,134 --> 00:22:29,037
♪ You really are a heel. ♪

493
00:22:29,104 --> 00:22:33,374
♪ You're as cuddly as a cactus,
you're as charming as an eel, ♪

494
00:22:33,442 --> 00:22:35,610
♪ Sue the Grinch. ♪

495
00:22:35,677 --> 00:22:42,917
♪ You're a bad banana with a...
A greasy black peel. ♪

496
00:22:48,023 --> 00:22:51,909
♪ You're a monster,
Sue the Grinch. ♪

497
00:22:51,994 --> 00:22:56,664
♪ Your heart's an empty hole. ♪

498
00:22:56,732 --> 00:22:58,032
♪ Your brain is full of spiders. ♪

499
00:22:58,083 --> 00:23:02,804
♪ You've got garlic in your soul,
Sue the Grinch. ♪

500
00:23:02,871 --> 00:23:08,543
♪ I wouldn't touch you with
a 39-and-a-half-foot pole. ♪

501
00:23:10,212 --> 00:23:14,615
♪ You're a foul one,
Sue the Grinch. ♪

502
00:23:14,683 --> 00:23:18,319
♪ You're a nasty, wasty skunk. ♪

503
00:23:18,387 --> 00:23:21,189
♪ Your heart is full of
unwashed socks. ♪

504
00:23:21,256 --> 00:23:24,292
♪ Your soul is full of gunk,
Sue the Grinch. ♪

505
00:23:28,313 --> 00:23:30,298
Becky, load it up.

506
00:23:34,336 --> 00:23:35,803
Santa?

507
00:23:35,871 --> 00:23:38,439
Why, Brittany.

508
00:23:38,507 --> 00:23:40,775
What are you doing here?

509
00:23:40,843 --> 00:23:44,378
I'm bringing a gift to put under
the tree for the homeless kids.

510
00:23:44,446 --> 00:23:45,813
It's a dollhouse.

511
00:23:45,881 --> 00:23:47,248
At least their dolls
won't be homeless.

512
00:23:48,317 --> 00:23:50,284
What are you doing, Santa?

513
00:23:50,352 --> 00:23:53,254
Well, you see, Brittany,
uh, one of the lights

514
00:23:53,305 --> 00:23:54,822
on the tree
isn't working.

515
00:23:54,890 --> 00:23:57,658
So I'm bringing it back
home to my workshop.

516
00:23:57,726 --> 00:24:00,728
I'll fix it up there,
and I'll bring it back here.

517
00:24:01,730 --> 00:24:02,497
Oh.

518
00:24:04,700 --> 00:24:06,968
Shuffle on home.

519
00:24:11,807 --> 00:24:13,641
(wheels squeaking)

520
00:24:26,814 --> 00:24:28,064
(school bell ringing)

521
00:24:28,149 --> 00:24:29,983
(whistling)

522
00:24:32,987 --> 00:24:34,287
They took everything.

523
00:24:34,355 --> 00:24:35,689
Including all of Sue's
Secret Santa gifts

524
00:24:35,756 --> 00:24:37,123
we were gonna give
to the homeless kids.

525
00:24:37,191 --> 00:24:38,625
RACHEL:
Only further proof

526
00:24:38,693 --> 00:24:40,427
that everyone in this school
hates us no matter what we do.

527
00:24:40,495 --> 00:24:42,028
It's not the school.

528
00:24:42,096 --> 00:24:43,363
It's Sue.
She did this.

529
00:24:43,431 --> 00:24:45,065
It wasn't Sue, it was Santa.

530
00:24:45,132 --> 00:24:46,933
He said a light was out on
the tree, he'd fix everything.

531
00:24:47,001 --> 00:24:48,168
We just need to let him
do his thing.

532
00:24:50,588 --> 00:24:53,673
Okay.

533
00:24:53,741 --> 00:24:55,008
Are you sure

534
00:24:55,076 --> 00:24:56,877
Santa was a boy
and not a girl, Brittany?

535
00:24:56,944 --> 00:24:58,061
I swear on my life.

536
00:24:58,145 --> 00:24:59,513
Santa's a boy.
Everybody knows that.

537
00:24:59,580 --> 00:25:01,047
It was probably one of the boys
on the football team.

538
00:25:03,217 --> 00:25:05,018
I guess it wasn't Sue.

539
00:25:05,086 --> 00:25:06,486
So our tree is gone.

540
00:25:06,554 --> 00:25:08,088
So our presents are missing.

541
00:25:08,155 --> 00:25:10,323
Santa's probably fixing any
dents or chips as we speak.

542
00:25:10,391 --> 00:25:13,093
FINN:
All around the world today,

543
00:25:13,160 --> 00:25:15,128
way worse things have happened
to people than this.

544
00:25:15,196 --> 00:25:17,497
Sorry, but I'm not going
to let this get us down.

545
00:25:18,933 --> 00:25:20,233
'Tis the season.

546
00:25:20,301 --> 00:25:22,202
I agree. Come on, guys,
let's clean this up.

547
00:25:24,422 --> 00:25:27,073
Come on.
(claps)

548
00:25:27,124 --> 00:25:28,842
Finn.

549
00:25:28,909 --> 00:25:30,844
You and I are
the leaders of this club.

550
00:25:30,912 --> 00:25:32,946
All right,
we need to fix this.

551
00:25:33,014 --> 00:25:34,948
We have to put everything
that's happened behind us

552
00:25:35,016 --> 00:25:37,934
and save Christmas
for the Glee Club.

553
00:25:38,019 --> 00:25:40,253
I want to make this right.

554
00:25:40,321 --> 00:25:42,923
(school bell ringing)

555
00:25:47,261 --> 00:25:49,279
You smell kind of funny.

556
00:25:49,363 --> 00:25:51,298
Oh, I, um,

557
00:25:51,365 --> 00:25:53,283
I put this on
for the car ride over.

558
00:25:53,367 --> 00:25:55,635
I know how much you love
the smell of Christmas pine.

559
00:25:55,703 --> 00:25:57,637
But guess I don't
really need it

560
00:25:57,705 --> 00:25:59,773
now that we have the real thing.

561
00:26:01,609 --> 00:26:03,476
It's so cold out.

562
00:26:03,544 --> 00:26:05,412
It's cuddle weather.

563
00:26:05,479 --> 00:26:08,415
It's unseasonably warm, actually,
for this time of year, but, uh...

564
00:26:08,466 --> 00:26:11,351
I just, I really wanted
to come here with you.

565
00:26:11,419 --> 00:26:14,154
I mean, the Christmas tree is
the foundation of Christmas.

566
00:26:14,221 --> 00:26:16,089
It's the hearth of
the Christmas home.

567
00:26:16,157 --> 00:26:18,558
Without it, there wouldn't be
anywhere to hang the ornaments

568
00:26:18,626 --> 00:26:20,560
or put the presents under.

569
00:26:20,628 --> 00:26:21,561
Yeah, yeah.

570
00:26:21,629 --> 00:26:22,896
Whenever we put the tree up,

571
00:26:22,964 --> 00:26:24,164
I always knew
Christmas was really here.

572
00:26:24,231 --> 00:26:27,100
This one's too small.

573
00:26:27,168 --> 00:26:28,568
- But, uh...
- Oh, I love this song.

574
00:26:28,636 --> 00:26:29,986
It's, uh, it's my
favorite Christmas song.

575
00:26:30,071 --> 00:26:31,004
It's Wham!

576
00:26:31,072 --> 00:26:32,522
Yeah, yeah.

577
00:26:32,607 --> 00:26:33,573
Cool.

578
00:26:33,641 --> 00:26:35,108
Um...

579
00:26:35,176 --> 00:26:36,977
I'm going to look down
this row of Frasier firs.

580
00:26:37,044 --> 00:26:38,912
Maybe you could
check out the Douglases

581
00:26:38,980 --> 00:26:40,614
and I'll meet you at the end.

582
00:26:40,681 --> 00:26:42,716
Okay.

583
00:26:42,783 --> 00:26:45,085
(Wham!'s "Last Christmas"
playing)

584
00:26:50,257 --> 00:26:54,361
♪ Last Christmas
I gave you my heart, ♪

585
00:26:54,428 --> 00:26:59,032
♪ but the very next day,
you gave it away. ♪

586
00:26:59,100 --> 00:27:03,470
♪ This year,
to save me from tears, ♪

587
00:27:03,537 --> 00:27:08,708
♪ I'll give it
to someone special. ♪

588
00:27:08,776 --> 00:27:12,912
♪ Once bitten and twice shy, ♪

589
00:27:12,980 --> 00:27:17,951
♪ I keep my distance,
but you still catch my eye. ♪

590
00:27:18,019 --> 00:27:21,354
♪ Tell me, baby,
do you recognize me? ♪

591
00:27:21,422 --> 00:27:23,723
♪ Oh... ♪
♪ Well, it's been a year... ♪

592
00:27:23,791 --> 00:27:26,893
♪ It doesn't surprise me. ♪

593
00:27:26,961 --> 00:27:27,861
♪ Christmas... ♪

594
00:27:27,928 --> 00:27:30,530
♪ I wrapped it up and sent it ♪

595
00:27:30,581 --> 00:27:32,699
♪ with a note saying ♪

596
00:27:32,767 --> 00:27:35,235
♪ "I love you," I meant it. ♪

597
00:27:35,302 --> 00:27:38,772
♪ Now I know
what a fool I've been. ♪

598
00:27:38,839 --> 00:27:41,241
♪ But if you kissed me now, ♪

599
00:27:41,308 --> 00:27:46,646
♪ I know you'd fool me again. ♪

600
00:27:46,645 --> 00:27:48,265
♪ Last Christmas,
I gave you my heart, ♪

601
00:27:48,282 --> 00:27:51,818
♪ And the very next day,
you gave it away. ♪

602
00:27:51,886 --> 00:27:52,719
♪ Gave it away... ♪

603
00:27:52,787 --> 00:27:57,657
♪ This year,
to save me from tears, ♪

604
00:27:57,725 --> 00:28:02,195
♪ I'll give it to someone special. ♪
♪ Oh, oh, oh... ♪

605
00:28:02,263 --> 00:28:05,699
♪ Last Christmas,
I gave you my heart... ♪

606
00:28:05,750 --> 00:28:08,001
♪ Oh, oh... ♪

607
00:28:08,068 --> 00:28:16,509
♪ You gave me away... ♪
♪ Oh... ♪

608
00:28:16,577 --> 00:28:21,815
♪ I'll give it to someone special. ♪

609
00:28:25,219 --> 00:28:28,288
Last year, for Christmas,

610
00:28:28,355 --> 00:28:29,789
I asked Santa to give me you.

611
00:28:36,781 --> 00:28:38,932
It's not last year anymore.

612
00:28:38,999 --> 00:28:40,767
It's Christmas, Finn.
It's time for you to forgive me.

613
00:28:40,818 --> 00:28:41,868
No, I can't.

614
00:28:43,237 --> 00:28:44,437
Okay, this is wrong.
I shouldn't...

615
00:28:44,505 --> 00:28:45,538
I shouldn't have
brought you here.

616
00:28:47,274 --> 00:28:48,608
You messed me up, Rachel.

617
00:28:48,676 --> 00:28:52,378
Can't you see
how screwed-up I am about this?

618
00:28:52,446 --> 00:28:54,914
I've had two girlfriends, and
both of them have cheated on me.

619
00:28:56,650 --> 00:29:00,887
Maybe you can ask Santa again
for me next year.

620
00:29:00,955 --> 00:29:02,722
I'm officially
breaking up with you.

621
00:29:13,138 --> 00:29:14,372
This was my dad's.

622
00:29:14,440 --> 00:29:17,375
He'd want you to do it.
For those kids.

623
00:29:20,346 --> 00:29:22,814
This was my uncle's.

624
00:29:22,881 --> 00:29:25,383
It's the first thing
I ever stole, actually.

625
00:29:27,019 --> 00:29:28,119
I'm going to look terrible.

626
00:29:28,187 --> 00:29:29,420
Shut up.
With your bone structure,

627
00:29:29,488 --> 00:29:30,772
you could rock
the <i>Rosemary's Baby</i> look

628
00:29:30,856 --> 00:29:32,557
and still look good.

629
00:29:32,625 --> 00:29:34,025
I'm going to look
like Jackie Chan.

630
00:29:34,093 --> 00:29:36,027
If Barbra can pull off a bob,
so can I.

631
00:29:36,095 --> 00:29:37,261
Enough yapping, let's do this.

632
00:29:37,329 --> 00:29:38,796
Whoa! Whoa!
What are you guys doing?

633
00:29:38,864 --> 00:29:40,765
We're going all "Gift of
the Magi" to raise money

634
00:29:40,833 --> 00:29:42,800
to buy homeless kids
those school supplies.

635
00:29:42,868 --> 00:29:44,636
The guys are gonna
sell their watches

636
00:29:44,703 --> 00:29:46,571
and the girls are gonna
sell off their hair.

637
00:29:46,639 --> 00:29:48,206
- You can't do that.
- Oh, no, it's cool.

638
00:29:48,273 --> 00:29:49,374
Most of this isn't mine,
anyways.

639
00:29:49,441 --> 00:29:50,875
No, I mean,
that's not the answer.

640
00:29:50,943 --> 00:29:53,044
There are other ways to raise
money at Christmastime.

641
00:29:53,112 --> 00:29:55,079
No, but we tried caroling,
and it didn't work.

642
00:29:55,147 --> 00:29:57,548
Wait, I thought you and Finn
were getting us a new tree.

643
00:29:57,616 --> 00:30:00,685
We went, but Finn bailed
before we could get one.

644
00:30:00,753 --> 00:30:02,553
Nice Christmas spirit, Finn.

645
00:30:02,621 --> 00:30:03,321
WILL:
Wait!

646
00:30:03,389 --> 00:30:05,189
Guys, no more fighting.

647
00:30:05,257 --> 00:30:06,691
(sighs)

648
00:30:06,759 --> 00:30:09,193
Have any of you ever actually
read "Gift of the Magi"?

649
00:30:11,430 --> 00:30:13,531
None of you?

650
00:30:13,599 --> 00:30:15,099
You don't have to read
"Gift of the Magi."

651
00:30:15,167 --> 00:30:16,100
everybody knows what it's about.

652
00:30:16,168 --> 00:30:18,102
Well, if you actually read it,

653
00:30:18,170 --> 00:30:19,637
you'd know what it's about.

654
00:30:19,705 --> 00:30:22,173
Yeah, I know what it's about:
Life freakin' sucks.

655
00:30:22,241 --> 00:30:23,607
Actually, you're right.

656
00:30:26,245 --> 00:30:27,478
The first Christmas
you remember having

657
00:30:27,546 --> 00:30:29,047
is the greatest day
of your life.

658
00:30:29,114 --> 00:30:30,515
Your family's all together,

659
00:30:30,582 --> 00:30:32,350
there are loads
of presents, cookies.

660
00:30:32,418 --> 00:30:33,885
The magic is
alive and well.

661
00:30:33,952 --> 00:30:37,822
But before you know it,
you grow up.

662
00:30:37,890 --> 00:30:40,258
Work and school
and girlfriends take over

663
00:30:40,325 --> 00:30:42,293
and Christmas becomes
more of an obligation,

664
00:30:42,361 --> 00:30:45,830
a reminder of what's lost
instead of what's possible.

665
00:30:45,898 --> 00:30:47,932
And all of the trees
and the presents

666
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:49,967
and even the mistletoe
can't change that.

667
00:30:50,035 --> 00:30:53,571
And then when
you get to my age...

668
00:30:53,639 --> 00:30:58,042
you're so desperate
to get that magic back,

669
00:30:58,110 --> 00:30:59,177
you'd do anything

670
00:30:59,244 --> 00:31:00,845
to be able to feel

671
00:31:00,913 --> 00:31:04,182
how you did
that first Christmas.

672
00:31:04,249 --> 00:31:05,116
So what should we do?

673
00:31:07,052 --> 00:31:10,988
Put your scissors down,
put your watches back on.

674
00:31:11,056 --> 00:31:12,724
We're gonna go out
and find some people

675
00:31:12,791 --> 00:31:14,392
who really need
some Christmas spirit,

676
00:31:14,460 --> 00:31:16,994
and we are gonna sing for them.

677
00:31:17,062 --> 00:31:20,882
Get a good night's rest, Ken,
you're gonna need it.

678
00:31:20,966 --> 00:31:23,501
Barbie took the early flight
from Tampa.

679
00:31:23,569 --> 00:31:24,502
(clattering)

680
00:31:32,644 --> 00:31:34,345
Santa?

681
00:31:36,048 --> 00:31:37,782
But it's too early.

682
00:31:37,850 --> 00:31:41,018
Well, you know what they say.

683
00:31:41,086 --> 00:31:43,121
Early's late if you make
tomorrow yesterday.

684
00:31:45,290 --> 00:31:46,224
Awesome.

685
00:31:46,291 --> 00:31:48,376
You know, Brittany,

686
00:31:48,460 --> 00:31:51,963
I was in the neighborhood,
doing a dry run.

687
00:31:52,030 --> 00:31:54,265
I have so many houses to
visit on Christmas Eve,

688
00:31:54,333 --> 00:31:56,334
I got to make sure it
goes off without a hitch.

689
00:31:56,401 --> 00:31:58,402
How about you come
sit with ol' Santy?

690
00:31:58,470 --> 00:32:00,371
(chuckles):
Okay!

691
00:32:00,422 --> 00:32:03,141
How about you sit next
to Santy instead?

692
00:32:03,208 --> 00:32:04,408
Santy's just a little stinky.

693
00:32:04,476 --> 00:32:06,144
(laughs)
He needs a good ol'

694
00:32:06,211 --> 00:32:07,278
sponge bath from Mrs. Claus.

695
00:32:07,346 --> 00:32:08,212
(chuckles)

696
00:32:11,183 --> 00:32:14,018
Brittany, do you remember what
you asked me for for Christmas?

697
00:32:14,086 --> 00:32:16,654
Yeah, I asked for Artie
to be able to walk.

698
00:32:19,892 --> 00:32:21,993
Is there anything else
that you want?

699
00:32:22,060 --> 00:32:22,994
I mean, like, anything?

700
00:32:23,061 --> 00:32:24,428
No.

701
00:32:24,496 --> 00:32:27,665
Well, see,
Santa's trying his best,

702
00:32:27,733 --> 00:32:29,967
but that one's
a little hard.

703
00:32:30,035 --> 00:32:32,537
But you're magic.

704
00:32:32,604 --> 00:32:34,472
Sometimes what Santa
wants to give

705
00:32:34,540 --> 00:32:36,607
a good girl like you is patience,

706
00:32:36,675 --> 00:32:38,109
because, believe it or not,

707
00:32:38,177 --> 00:32:39,844
there are even some things
that he can't manage.

708
00:32:39,912 --> 00:32:41,646
You know,

709
00:32:41,713 --> 00:32:44,582
there was a girl
a little younger than you

710
00:32:44,650 --> 00:32:46,217
and she was a little husky.

711
00:32:46,285 --> 00:32:48,786
She was always asking
Santy for the same thing:

712
00:32:48,854 --> 00:32:52,790
To make her look
more like the other girls.

713
00:32:52,858 --> 00:32:55,726
She wasn't asking to be
pretty or nothing.

714
00:32:55,794 --> 00:32:58,095
But she just didn't want
to stick out so much.

715
00:32:59,865 --> 00:33:03,734
Santa just couldn't do it.

716
00:33:03,802 --> 00:33:07,705
So instead Santa
gave her patience.

717
00:33:07,773 --> 00:33:09,373
And later on, that girl was...

718
00:33:09,441 --> 00:33:13,811
Was glad that Santy didn't give
her what she had asked him for.

719
00:33:13,879 --> 00:33:17,648
She... She put being
husky to good use.

720
00:33:17,716 --> 00:33:20,117
Was her name Ricki Lake?

721
00:33:20,185 --> 00:33:22,620
(sighs)
The point is...

722
00:33:22,688 --> 00:33:25,523
I don't think I'm going
to be able to give you

723
00:33:25,591 --> 00:33:27,925
what you're asking for,
even though I'd like to.

724
00:33:27,993 --> 00:33:30,294
- But, Santa...
- I'm sorry, pumpkin.

725
00:33:30,362 --> 00:33:32,363
It's... It's just not
going to happen.

726
00:33:35,400 --> 00:33:37,101
Aren't you going
to go up the chimney?

727
00:33:39,304 --> 00:33:42,940
On dry runs,
Santy uses the Isuzu.

728
00:33:54,787 --> 00:33:56,338
(school bell ringing)

729
00:33:59,474 --> 00:34:00,708
What's going on?

730
00:34:00,776 --> 00:34:03,377
I think I've lost
the Christmas spirit.

731
00:34:05,547 --> 00:34:07,148
It's Santa.

732
00:34:07,215 --> 00:34:08,983
I don't know if
I can tell you.

733
00:34:13,555 --> 00:34:15,956
I used to believe that
Santa could do anything.

734
00:34:16,076 --> 00:34:17,596
If Santa isn't magical,

735
00:34:17,716 --> 00:34:20,161
I don't even know if I
want to believe anymore.

736
00:34:20,228 --> 00:34:22,596
It isn't fair that you
can't walk, Artie.

737
00:34:22,664 --> 00:34:24,298
I feel so terrible.

738
00:34:24,366 --> 00:34:29,937
Hey, look at me.
I'm fine.

739
00:34:30,005 --> 00:34:32,707
Hey, guys, we need you
in the teachers' lounge.

740
00:34:32,774 --> 00:34:35,543
Mr. Shue...
Brittany's not feeling so good.

741
00:34:35,610 --> 00:34:36,911
Santa thing.

742
00:34:36,978 --> 00:34:38,612
If you don't mind,
I think I'm going

743
00:34:38,680 --> 00:34:40,481
to take her home,
make sure she's okay.

744
00:34:40,549 --> 00:34:42,416
Good idea. We'll
make do without you.

745
00:34:46,888 --> 00:34:49,190
(school bell ringing)

746
00:34:49,257 --> 00:34:52,226
Hey, uh, so we're your students.

747
00:34:52,294 --> 00:34:55,796
All year long you suffer
through dealing with us.

748
00:34:55,864 --> 00:34:58,566
I imagine having some of us
in your classes

749
00:34:58,633 --> 00:35:01,035
would slowly chip away at
your hopes and dreams,

750
00:35:01,103 --> 00:35:03,137
until the whole world just felt
like a never-ending

751
00:35:03,205 --> 00:35:05,873
- nightmare of pain...
- Just get to the point, Finn.

752
00:35:05,941 --> 00:35:08,509
Right. Uh, anyway,
we're here today

753
00:35:08,577 --> 00:35:09,944
to help raise money

754
00:35:10,011 --> 00:35:12,279
for children that have a lot
less than we do.

755
00:35:12,330 --> 00:35:15,349
And I know some of us
have had a hard Christmas,

756
00:35:15,417 --> 00:35:17,918
but what we've come to learn
is that no matter

757
00:35:17,986 --> 00:35:19,353
how tough things get,

758
00:35:19,421 --> 00:35:21,122
there isn't anything
that more Santa

759
00:35:21,189 --> 00:35:23,791
or a couple more jingle bells
can't cure.

760
00:35:23,859 --> 00:35:26,127
SUE:
Well, Becky, we did it.

761
00:35:26,194 --> 00:35:28,996
We got all my presents back.

762
00:35:29,064 --> 00:35:31,065
And as satisfying
as it is to have been

763
00:35:31,133 --> 00:35:33,968
gifted enough rotisserie ovens
to roast an entire hobo...

764
00:35:34,035 --> 00:35:37,438
For me,
the real joy of Christmas

765
00:35:37,506 --> 00:35:39,607
was breaking the collective
heart of the Glee Club.

766
00:35:39,674 --> 00:35:43,611
(gentle melodic music playing)

767
