♪ Fahoo fores, dahoo dores. ♪

786
00:37:10,966 --> 00:37:15,603
♪ Welcome, Christmas,
bring your light. ♪

787
00:37:15,670 --> 00:37:18,656
♪ Ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh... ♪

788
00:37:18,740 --> 00:37:22,643
♪ Ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh,
ooh-ooh-ooh... ♪

789
00:37:22,711 --> 00:37:26,080
Christmas came anyway, Coach.

790
00:37:26,147 --> 00:37:28,883
It's beautiful.

791
00:37:31,620 --> 00:37:33,520
It is.

792
00:37:42,797 --> 00:37:45,649
(school bell ringing)

793
00:37:45,734 --> 00:37:46,867
How much did we raise?

794
00:37:46,935 --> 00:37:48,468
210 bucks.

795
00:37:48,520 --> 00:37:49,870
And that's after my cut.

796
00:37:49,938 --> 00:37:51,171
I'm kidding.

797
00:37:51,239 --> 00:37:52,273
Now that you're divorced

798
00:37:52,324 --> 00:37:53,807
and Ms. Pillsbury
married another guy,

799
00:37:53,875 --> 00:37:55,709
I guess you'll be spending
Christmas Eve alone.

800
00:37:55,777 --> 00:37:57,144
Yes, Rachel, I am.

801
00:37:57,212 --> 00:37:59,713
Well, I know how painful
being alone can feel,

802
00:37:59,781 --> 00:38:02,182
so if you want,
you can come over to my house.

803
00:38:02,250 --> 00:38:04,184
We're going to eat Chinese
and watch <i>The Main Event</i>.

804
00:38:04,252 --> 00:38:06,670
Thanks, Rachel.
I think I'm going to pass.

805
00:38:06,755 --> 00:38:08,589
Nothing wrong
with being alone.

806
00:38:16,798 --> 00:38:18,599
Artie.

807
00:38:18,667 --> 00:38:19,733
(mechanical whirring)

808
00:38:19,801 --> 00:38:21,535
(gasps)

809
00:38:25,407 --> 00:38:27,775
It's called a ReWalk.

810
00:38:27,842 --> 00:38:30,244
Some guy in Israel
invented it.

811
00:38:30,312 --> 00:38:33,080
I can't use it
all the time, but...

812
00:38:33,148 --> 00:38:34,982
Check me out.

813
00:38:38,353 --> 00:38:40,454
(whirring)

814
00:38:53,068 --> 00:38:55,069
Where did you get it?

815
00:38:55,136 --> 00:38:59,640
BRITTANY: We went home and
it was sitting under my Christmas tree.

816
00:38:59,708 --> 00:39:01,225
How the hell did you
afford that thing?

817
00:39:01,309 --> 00:39:02,176
BRITTANY:
I didn't buy it.

818
00:39:02,243 --> 00:39:03,610
I didn't know what it was.

819
00:39:03,678 --> 00:39:05,245
I thought it was
a Transformer.

820
00:39:05,313 --> 00:39:07,548
I assumed her dad
got it for me,

821
00:39:07,615 --> 00:39:10,184
but he has no idea
where it came from.

822
00:39:10,251 --> 00:39:12,086
He went to take
a long poop, and when

823
00:39:12,153 --> 00:39:13,821
he came back it was there.

824
00:39:13,888 --> 00:39:15,489
So if no one we know
bought it for you, then...

825
00:39:15,557 --> 00:39:17,057
Santa brought it.

826
00:39:18,760 --> 00:39:20,427
Santa.

827
00:39:20,495 --> 00:39:22,363
Santa.

828
00:39:24,933 --> 00:39:26,600
A real Christmas miracle.

829
00:39:30,805 --> 00:39:32,639
(whirring)

830
00:39:47,856 --> 00:39:49,723
(school bell ringing)

831
00:40:06,541 --> 00:40:08,409
(fire crackling)

832
00:40:17,919 --> 00:40:19,887
Hey, Will.

833
00:40:22,290 --> 00:40:24,358
How...How did you get in here?

834
00:40:24,426 --> 00:40:25,926
Oh, I had a key made
ages ago.

835
00:40:26,995 --> 00:40:28,295
How do you like your tree?

836
00:40:30,365 --> 00:40:32,800
Uh, it's... It's...
It's beautiful.

837
00:40:32,867 --> 00:40:35,335
Wh... What's going on?
What's with all the presents?

838
00:40:35,403 --> 00:40:37,571
Well, you remember that
old meanie who stole

839
00:40:37,639 --> 00:40:39,606
all that stuff out
of the choir room?

840
00:40:39,674 --> 00:40:42,476
Well, she's sorry.

841
00:40:42,544 --> 00:40:44,678
Really?

842
00:40:44,746 --> 00:40:47,414
And what made her
change her mind?

843
00:40:47,482 --> 00:40:48,982
I don't know.

844
00:40:49,050 --> 00:40:50,951
Call it a Christmas miracle
and we'll leave it at that.

845
00:40:51,002 --> 00:40:54,621
Now I know a lot of these gifts
are for orphans or something,

846
00:40:54,689 --> 00:40:58,025
but, uh... I got you
something special.

847
00:40:58,093 --> 00:40:59,593
It's okay, it's not
going to explode.

848
00:41:05,333 --> 00:41:08,602
I thought you might want to put
all of us out of our misery

849
00:41:08,670 --> 00:41:10,137
and shave off that Chia Pet.

850
00:41:13,341 --> 00:41:15,175
Thanks, Sue.

851
00:41:15,243 --> 00:41:17,111
The tree really does look great.

852
00:41:17,178 --> 00:41:19,313
Well, Santa had some helpers.

853
00:41:19,380 --> 00:41:21,782
(whistle blowing)

854
00:41:24,185 --> 00:41:27,688
No one should be alone
on Christmas Eve, Mr. Schuester.

855
00:41:27,755 --> 00:41:30,057
SUE: Too much talking, lady,
not enough trimming.

856
00:41:30,125 --> 00:41:33,026
Come on, let's get some
Christmas up in here.

857
00:41:36,264 --> 00:41:38,432
I thought you
hated the holidays.

